{
  "texts": [
    "A schematic of data flow during tile extraction is shown in Fig. 1.",
    "Image tiles can be buffered into binary TFRecord format, an efficient storage format that improves dataset iteration speed compared to iterating directly from WSIs.",
    "Image data can be encoded using either JPEG (lossy) or PNG (lossless) compression.",
    "Image tiles are extracted in a grid, with optional overlap or jitter for data augmentation.",
    "During tile extraction, images tiles can undergo an additional filtering step using either grayspace or whitespace filtering, potentially identifying tiles with high background content that were not successfully removed by Otsu's thresholding."
  ]
}